  "text": "Fluorescent labelling of Drosophila heart structures was performed as described [CITATION_1] . In brief, semi-intact heart preparations of four flies of each genotype were fixed in 4% formaldehyde (Fisher Scientific, Loughborough, UK) in PBS for 20 mins then 3610 min washes with PBS-Triton-X (PBST)(Sigma, Poole, Dorset, UK). Hearts were then incubated with primary antibodies and/or stained in PBST overnight at 4uC with constant agitation. Hearts were washed 3610 mins in PBST, incubated with secondary antibodies for 1-hour at room temp, washed 3610 mins in PBST plus final wash in PBS alone. Hearts were then mounted in 50% glycerol (Sigma, Poole, Dorset, UK) in PBS and visualised using a Zeiss Axioskop 2 mot plus fluorescent microscope and images were taken using Openlab imaging software. Anti-bPSintegrin (1:10 of hybridoma supernatant (100 mg/ml), Developmental Studies Hybridoma Bank) was used to stain cell junctions, AlexaFluor 546-conjugated phalloidin (13.2 nM) to stain F-actin (Invitrogen, Paisley, UK), and DAPI (1 ng/ml) to stain nuclei (Sigma, Poole, Dorset, UK). The hybridoma developed by [CITATION_2] was obtained from the Developmental Studies Hybridoma Bank developed under the auspices of the NICHD and maintained by The University of Iowa, Department of Biology, Iowa City, IA 52242.",
